The paper deals with privacy-preserving mechanisms for releasing statistics of real-valued data streams, which is a topic that falls under the category of privacy and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the optimization of utility in the release of the threshold, which involves machine learning techniques (cs.LG). The paper also deals with the estimation of the threshold, which is a problem in data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). Finally, the paper discusses the use of differential privacy, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
